  "instructions": [
    "Combine ground lamb, onion salt, breadcrumbs, parsley, garlic, spices, and salt in a large bowl, mixing well by hand until just combined.",
    "Cover the mixture and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.",
    "Preheat the yakimono-grill or grill pan to medium-high heat, about 400°F (200°C).",
    "Using your hands, shape the mixture into 8-10 small meatballs, about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.",
    "Place the meatballs on the preheated grill and cook for 3-4 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through.",
    "Transfer the meatballs to a plate and let rest for 5 minutes before serving."
